p: Monocyclic monoterpenes/monoterpenoids (α-terpinolene, terpinen-4-ol, cryptone, α-terpineol, trans-carveol, cis-carveol) are the next subclass of the monoterpenes class found in this study. The concentrations of the eucalyptol, α-terpinolene, β-linalool, and cis-verbenol were highest in the 0–5 min DT fractions ( Table 7 and Table 8), whereas the concentrations of trans-pinocarveol and pinocarvone were the highest in the control oil ( Table 8). The concentrations of terpinen-4-ol, cryptone, trans-carveol, verbenone, and cis-carveol reached their max in the 40–60 min DT fraction ( Table 9).
